OL,7,FRMT workers have voted to formally
OL,8,Freject Network Rail's offer of a nine
OL,9,Fper cent pay rise over the next two
OL,10,Fyears in a bid to avert strike action.
OL,12,FThe union said that 63.6 per cent of
OL,13,Fmembers voted to reject the Network
OL,14,FRail offer on an 83 per cent turnout.
OL,15,FThe public body, overseen by the
OL,16,FDepartment for Transport, had offered a
OL,17,Ffive per cent pay rise in 2022
OL,18,Fbackdated to January, and a four per
OL,19,Fcent pay rise from the start of 2023.
OL,3,CTrain strikes to continue as RMT
OL,4,Cworkers reject 9 per cent pay rise
OL,5,Coffer from Network Rail
